The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Shoppers to raise Rs 500cr 
                                                                                                               Shoppers to raise Rs 500cr 
          SOHINI MOOKHERJEA                                                Cash Course      
	Calcutta, March 24: Shoppers Stop Limited will raise Rs 500 crore through a rights issue to part fund its expansion plans.        
	The retail major plans to invest Rs 1,500 crore by 2011 to ramp up its presence across various brands. Shoppers will increase its retail space to seven million sqft by 2011 from 1.7 million sqft.        
	Indian retail is slowly being recognised globally and though we have a long way to go, this is the time for tremendous growth. We also plan to grow aggressively across the country. We will part-fund the investment through a rights issue, the documentation for which is under way, said B.S. Nagesh, managing director of Shoppers Stop Limited.        
	Apart from the rights issue, the company will raise Rs 500 crore through debt or borrowings and the remaining Rs 500 crore of the Rs 1,500-crore investment will come from internal accruals.         
	The company is set to reach the Rs 1,000-crore turnover mark by the end of this fiscal.        
	Shoppers Stop will have more than 50 outlets while another 25 outlets will be added to the Hypercity format.        
	Shoppers Stop operates Mothercare stores in India under franchise from Mothercare of the UK. It plans to open 100 Mothercare outlets in India.                                                                                                                                        
